{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem is decomposed into checking the existence of k(n)=1, then k(n)=2, and finally k(n)=3 based on the properties of the number 2023.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Determine if there exists an integer n such that 2023*n is a power of 2. Use the prime factorization of 2023 to justify your answer. This corresponds to checking if k(n)=1 is possible."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Determine if k(n)=2 is possible by checking if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b for some integers a, b. Specifically, check if 2023 divides 2^m + 1 for some m. If k(n)=2 is impossible, investigate if k(n)=3 is possible (i.e., check if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b + 2^c for some integers a, b, c)."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent agent will take the results from helper_1 and helper_2 to find the smallest integer k in {1, 2, 3, ...} that is achievable. If helper_1 says k(n)=1 is impossible and helper_2 finds k(n)=2 is impossible but k(n)=3 is possible, the final answer is 3."
}
```

